<TITLE> Mother, daughter killed in Lalmonirhat fire </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Lalmonirhat, Mar 07 (bdnews24.com)  A mother and daughter were killed in a fire at a village in Lalmonirhat on Saturday night. The deceased have been identified as Shefali Begum, 42, and daughter Bithika, 7, of Char Matukpur village of Kaliganj upazila. Neighbour Saiful Islam told bdnews24.com that the fire broke out at around 1am at a cow-shed on his property and later spread to five other homes in the area. Bithika was asleep in bed when the fire broke out; Shefali was killed as she went inside her burning house to bring the child out, Islam said. Kaliganj upazila fire service station officer Abdur Rauf said fire vehicles could not reach the spot in time as there were no accessible roads. Locals and fire fighters said that flammable materials placed near to unguarded mosquito coils may have been the cause of the fire. b
